OK, firstly Iâ€™d like to thank you all sincerely for playing my game, even though it didnâ€™t go at all how Iâ€™d intended it to!Â  You all committed your time and energy to this and for that I am very grateful.
o give you some background to this game, there were 3 mainaims I was going for:

1)Â Â Â Â Â To test out the Amulet of Peace â€“ my prize for lynching Town in ext-342. :DÂ  I stuck the Harpy in because this would potentially give two sets of shroud/silence in the day.
2)Â Â Â Â Â To test out the Banshee in anger â€“ I wanted to see how much fun it could have, and to see how it helped get the UD their lynches.

3)      To show people that they should keep on playing in the GY because Iâ€™ve seen a few losses recently where teammates spilled the beans when they were dead, which adversely affected their teamâ€™s chances after a revive.  The hope was that people would be popping in and out of the GY and you wouldnâ€™t know who to trust, since we had the Witch, Reviver and Ankh, Banshee, Medium, plus the Succubus for redirects.  i.e. donâ€™t give up playing once youâ€™re â€˜deadâ€™!

Each faction had a stealing potion, and there were plenty of killing items and resto pots to be had (not to mention the amulet!), and agitate potential that could have helped thin out the numbers earlier on when claims hadnâ€™t been so verified.  The stalkers/GDs/militia-crossbows were also intended to create vamp-paranoia, which did happen.

Regarding the early lack of deaths, this was partially down to RNG bad luck, and also Evuls taking each other out.  On N1, the Killing Ghoul was stalked to the (failed) kill on Cherry and then claimed Vanilla, therefore taking the UDâ€™s stealing pot to the grave with him.  The Warlock also marked the Zombie, meaning that Coven â€˜killedâ€™ the Zombie on N2 when it was dying anyway.

Meanwhile on N2, the VD zombified my poor PM and took him and the puppets out straight away, removing what was shaping up to be a comedic masterpiece by Henners I felt.  This loss sucked especially as Henners had requested twice on N1 for the Djinn to swap him into another avatar, but the instruction wasnâ€™t seen/done.
All this meant that Evuls had a really rough start.

The Undead team seemed to more or less destroy themselves.  In hindsight I should have delayed the game so that the Meet Up guys were home before it started, but even when everyone was â€˜backâ€™, the night chat was relatively quiet.

Everyone (including the UD team) seemed to be focussed on removing Marc the Banshee from the game asap, despite him pleading nightly not to let him die so early.  Adding insult to injury, Marc was lobbed the Disruption Orb by his teammate on the night he was shot by Shaneâ€™s (non-rusty) crossbow, thus becoming perma-blocked in the GY and unable to execute the Bansheeâ€™s main role.  So much for my Banshee test!

Coven meanwhile had a rather unlucky time in their own right and should really have had a better game.  This was out of our control, but we did try to rebalance things for fairness.  They made a great move in stealing the Amulet, so it was interesting to see how they handled that, especially on the day of the third agitation and there were only 3 stacks towards the end of day, with two of those shroudedâ€¦

In the very end it came down to two choices on the last night.  CabbagePultâ€™s decision to finally shoot, and where Coven used their redirect â€“ weighing up between self-shrouding the Harpy and redirecting the final militia.  Coven decided to redirect the Harpy on to themselves for the shroud, meanwhile passing the Amulet to the Succubusâ€¦.who got shot by the militia, taking the Amulet to the grave with them, thus ending their shot at immortlity.
